Paul John HUNT, Appellant, v. SECURITIES EXCHANGE COMMISSION, Appellee. No. 11419. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Jan. 16, 1947. Rehearing Denied Feb. 14, 1947. Lewie Williams and Fred’k R. Burch, both of Seattle, Wash., for appellant. Roger S. Foster, Sol., Robert S. Rubin, Associate Sol., Milton P. Kroll, Sp. Asst., and Myer Feldman, Atty., SEC., all of Philadelphia, Pa. (James E. Newton, Atty., SEC., of Seattle, Wash. of counsel), for appellee.

Before DENMAN, STEPHENS, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed. Shaw v. United States, 9 Cir., 1942, 131 F.2d 476, 480.
